content: Dang, this game has been quite the journey. Gave up the first time I tried it and I picked it up again around 3 weeks ago. Was determined to finish it this time and I finally managed to. I love this game's design and aesthetic, and I love how such simple controls can create such dynamic situations and gameplay. Also, despite what I've seen elsewhere, I actually found the commentary to be a great addition. The controls are a bit wonky sometimes, but overall would totally recommend getting it!

A game inspired by a simple B-Game that came out in 2008, entitled 'Sexy Hiking'. The objective of the game is to simply drag yourself up a mountain using a hammer. The mountain itself is a rough assemblage of seemingly random objects and assets from other games and areas. The player has to make their way up the unforgiving heap whilst constantly being at the risk of falling and losing everything.
